{
  "_comment": "Channel Limits Database - defines safety limits and verification for runtime validation. All 168 writable :SP addresses from the namespace-union manifest (docker/virtual-accelerator/manifest) are covered below, family-banded from the SR lattice model's device inventory and machine.json's simulated nominal values (see docker/virtual-accelerator/lattice/response.py for the SR corrector +-10A convention that sizes the HCM/VCM band; other families use a generous band around their machine.json nominal spread).",
  "_version": "2.0",
  "_description": "This database configures automatic limits validation and verification for channel writes. The connector reads this configuration and applies it automatically - capabilities don't need to know about these details. Note: max_step is intentionally NOT set on the real channels below -- LimitsValidator's max_step check reads the current value via a direct pyepics caget regardless of connector type (not connector-abstracted), which would block every write to these channels in the default mock control-system type (no live EPICS server behind mock addresses). min/max bounds plus readback verification below already enforce 'value must fit inside its own limits' without that failure mode.",
  "defaults": {
    "_comment": "Default settings inherited by all channels unless overridden",
    "writable": true,
    "verification": {
      "level": "callback",
      "_comment": "Default verification: callback (fast, EPICS IOC confirmation)"
    }
  },
